               <msContents>
                  <summary>Manuscript in a late 19th century hand, containing canticle of the flower, lamentations of the Virgin, image of Mary, and image of the Trinity.
                     Ff. 3r–41v: Canticle of the flower, Maḫleta Ṣege, ማሕሌተ ጽጌ. Many sections are numbered (e.g., sections 27 and following from folios 9 and following; Ff. 42r–55v: Lamentations of the Virgin, ሰቆቃወ ድንግል; Ff. 56r–76r: Image of Mary, Salam Leki, Maryam, ሰላም ለኪ ማርይም ድንግል ዘመዓዛ አፉኪ ኮል, used during Passion week, arranged for the hours of the day; Ff. 77r–89v: Image of the Trinity, Malk‘a Śellase, መልክአ ሥላሴ, incipit : ሰላም ለሕላዌክሙ ዘይመውእ ህላዌያተ.
                  </summary>
